window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><i>Daniel is my son. He has always been mine. And he always will be.</i> </p> <p>On some level deep inside, Laura Bateman knows something is wrong. That her relationship with her son is not what it should be. That it is based on lies. </p> <p>But bad things have happened to Laura. Things that change a person. Forever. </p> <p>For twenty-six-year-old Daniel, the discovery that his mother is not who he thought comes close to destroying him. As his world turns upside down, he searches for sanity in the madness that has become his life. Daniel is left with nothing but questions. Why did Laura do something so terrible? Can he move past the demons of his childhood? </p> <p>And the biggest question of all: can he ever forgive Laura? </p>"; 
